com.appittome.udacity.client
Class UdacityCourseList.Course

java.lang.Object
  com.appittome.udacity.client.UdacityCourseList.Course
Enclosing class:
UdacityCourseList
public class UdacityCourseList.Course
extends java.lang.Object

Class to represent members of the CourseList object: courses. Upon instantiation, each course list will try to perform an async GET course.get, and then parse its unit, and nugget lists.

NOTE: The response to the GET course.get action is a rather bulky object, and parsing it takes some time. Right now this is all implemented to happen in one huge lump: parse the entire object, organize the list of units, for each set of units organize a list of lists of nuggets.

With a custom parser the response could be broken down, and portions parsed individualy so that the UI could be updated more fluidly. Then the most pianful porition of the wait would only be the 20-30k object download.

startNuggetSortTask

public void startNuggetSortTask()
Override to implement custom scheduling of nugget population. Currently this method takes the unitList of this course as an array and passes it to a single async process that moves through the list linearly until it has populated the nugget list for each unit with all the available lists for each topic.
